==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enrage
<hw>En*rage"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Enraged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Enraging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>enrager</ets> to be enraged; pref. <ets>en-</ets> (L.
<ets>in</ets>) + <ets>rage</ets> rage. See <er>Rage</er>.]</ety> <def>To
fill with rage; to provoke to frenzy or madness; to make
furious.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To irritate; incense; inflame; exasperate;
provoke; anger; madden; infuriate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>enraged</ent>⟦br⟧
